description: EU states are portrayed as feuding but the 27 leaders believe they have more in common than apart.
title: Coronavirus: Why fractious EU still believes together is better
title_page: Coronavirus: Why fractious EU still believes together is better - BBC News
maintext: Following their Thursday summit, EU leaders will ask the European Commission to come up with concrete proposals but insiders say the painful process of compromise over the fund and the new EU budget is only likely to happen when leaders sit together in person. And who knows when that will next be?
